# SEO & AEO Standards — miklat.co.il

## Primary keywords
- **HE:** מקלט קרוב, מקלט ציבורי, מציאת מקלט, ממ"ד קרוב
- **EN:** nearest public shelter Israel, bomb shelter finder Israel
- **RU:** ближайшее укрытие Израиль

## Atomic Answer rule
Every content change to `index.html` must preserve the hidden `#seo-content` article.
The first `<p>` inside it must remain a **40–60 word direct answer** to the primary query.

## Meta tags — required fields
Always keep ALL of these in `<head>`:
- `<title>` — include primary keyword + number (e.g. "41,525 מקלטים")
- `<meta name="description">` — 140–160 chars, include keyword + differentiator
- `<link rel="canonical">`
- `<link rel="alternate" hreflang="he|en|ru|x-default">`
- `<meta property="og:*">` and `<meta name="twitter:*">`

## JSON-LD — always update `dateModified`
When editing `index.html`, update `"dateModified"` in the WebApplication schema
to the current date (YYYY-MM-DD).

## H2s must be questions (voice-search)
In the `#seo-content` article every `<h2>` must be a natural-language question.
Follow every H2 with a `<p><em>Key Takeaway: …</em></p>`.

## Structured data every 500 words
Any prose section > 500 characters must include at least one:
- `<table>` comparison, OR
- `<ol>` / `<ul>` list

## Entity-rich language
Prefer entity names over generic terms:
✅ "GovMap (CC-BY)", "פיקוד העורף", "Leaflet.markercluster", "Haversine distance"
❌ "government site", "the official body", "the map library"

## llms.txt — keep in sync
After any meaningful content change, update `llms.txt`:
- Update the shelter count if it changes
- Update the Atomic Answer paragraph
- Add any new third-party service to the Entities section

## Do NOT
- Add `display:none` or `visibility:hidden` to `#seo-content` (use sr-only clip instead)
- Remove the FAQPage schema
- Shorten `<meta name="description">` below 140 characters
